The article announces a historic commitment between Serbia and Kosovo towards economic normalization. After years of failed negotiations, the two countries have reached a breakthrough by focusing on job creation and economic growth. Additionally, progress has been made in achieving peace in the Middle East, with Kosovo and Israel agreeing to normalize ties and establish diplomatic relations. Serbia has committed to opening a commercial office in Jerusalem this month and moving its embassy to Jerusalem by July. The article acknowledges the bravery of President Vučić of Serbia and Prime Minister Hoti of Kosovo in embarking on these talks. The author expresses hope for the prosperity of Serbia and Kosovo as they work together on economic cooperation in the region.